<br>
I had no clarity, so I was trying to optimize my use of right click nukes(Boots of Bladecalling).  I managed to keep my mana regenerating the entire time.  There was no &quot;full mana&quot; time.  I decided to try to put Kindir and his sceptre/ancient spell into my shoes, just to see what I'd get.  <br>
<br>
I found that I cast BoBC 165 times(17 seconds per), sofb 81 times(5.8 per), and FoT 3 times (7 per).  For a moment let's ignore mana.  I spent 3295.8 seconds casting spells.  Kindir figured 12.1 seconds per cast cycle, and you could fit 272.4 of those cycles into the time I spent casting.  At 1500 damage per cycle that would be 408,000 damage.<br>
<br>
My resist rate was about 6%.  I think it is more than reasonable to assume crits would make up for this.  I think 408,000 is reasonable as far as resists are concerned.<br>
<br>
Ok to summarize the numbers(and add a couple of missing ones:<br>
<br>
Camp session:  7714 seconds<br>
Time main warrior spent in combat: 4707 seconds.<br>
Time spent casting spells: 3295.8 seconds.<br>
Damage dealt:  408,000<br>
DPS (vs. the Main Tank):  86.7<br>
DPS (vs. the total session):  52.9<br>
<br>
Now, my realized DPS versus the main tank was only 39.  The huge difference comes from two main sources.  First, we ruled out mana regeneration and assumed Kindir would be using the click nuke and mana nuke an equal amount, whereas I had no clarity and used my boots almost exclusively.  Second, the ancient nuke has a higher dps, which would allow for more click damage assuming it was able to equal the damage done by shock of fiery blades.<br>
<br>
We can't -know- how mana would have limited Kindir, but we could guess.  I'm going to assume 33% reduction in mana cost (21% spec, 12% focus item)..  Sorry, but I think that is being somewhat generous.  In order for him to maintain the 86.7 dps vs. the MT quoted above, he would need to have 51938 mana in 7714 seconds, which is 40 mana per tick.<br>
<br>
Figure 11.5 per tick if you had a horse (7714-3295.8 to figure out time spend medding) That's if medding is 20 mana per tick.<br>
<br>
Then 4 from TPP.<br>
Then 14 from KEI, we're at 29.5 per tick.<br>
<br>
10.5 per tick from rods and flowing thought.  (Maybe 5 from rods.. and hell even I have FT 6.)<br>
<br>
Not too tough IMO.  The only thing is the fairly generous focus item figure, but even then you'd only need another 4 FT to make up for it.<br>
<br>
In order to achieve 125 dps versus the MT using my amount of time spent casting, you'd have to spend a lot more mana though.  Where I had you nuking 272 times with the sceptre and 272 times with the ancient nuke, to deal 125 dps instead of 86.6 you'd have to nuke 440 times with the ancient and 150 times with the sceptre.  This would up the required mana regen to 65.<br>
<br>
<br>
If your pet was doing 75dps, then I would say yes, 200 dps relative to another melee is at least in the realm of possibility.<br>
<br>
200dps is only uptime dps though, this would not be sustainable to infinity.  Given the uptime/downtime ratio, the 200dps in combat would be only 122 sustained..   But umm imo 122 sustained is fricking insanely high anyway so /shrug.  <br>
<br>
Flaws I see with this hypothesis:<br>
<br>
1.  Theoretically, up to 4707 seconds could have been spent casting spells.  In my experience, it isn't feasible to cast nukes for 100% of combat time,  but others may experience differently.<br>
<br>
2.  Switching me out with someone dealing a higher DPS, you'd change the conditions of the group.  The effect this would have on the analysis is unknown to me.  Perhaps it would lead to more downtime, perhaps less, perhaps the same with more mobs killed.  Hard to say. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2497<br> <font color=#333333>(11/28/02 7:15:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7965.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Is 200dps sustained Possible?</span><hr size=1> btw I have read that thread from Mikar several times before, it's extremely annoying trying to sort out the discussion.  When you research something you typically summarize your methods and organize your results.  That thread is like listening in on a discussion and seeing some people's personal notes.  Of course now I'll go ahead and do the same thing, but this post won't get stuck in a library.<br>
<br>
For my test, I buffed myself with TPP and wore FT6(+10 mana regen).  I nuked myself oom, casting burn repeatedly until I got the insuffecient mana message.  I stood and timed myself standing until I reached 100% mana.  With FT10 and innate standing +1 my mana pool came out to be 3395 if it maxes at the beginning of the 100%, or 3430 if it maxed at the end of 100%.<br>
<br>
Magelo tells me I should have 3333 mana.  Honestly, my guess is that this is where they made their error.<br>
<br>
I then nuked myself to insuffecient mana with SoFB and logged the time, and after that nuked myself to insuffecient mana with burn.  I used several different methods to account for the mana left over after I recieved the &quot;insuffecient mana&quot; message, and the only case where I was able to round up to even 20% was if I assumed less than 4% savings on burn.  In no case was I ever over 19.8%<br>
<br>
I did come up with 21% savings if I used the 3333 figure for my mana pool and used 10% or lower savings on burn.<br>
<br>
From what I read of that thread, no one did a full, raw mana pool test, and the mana pool is a rather important variable.  The good figures I got from that were only relative to normal specialization.<br>
<br>
The ShowEQ guy did not use SCM3, he only used 2.  From what I could tell he just made an educated guess.<br>
<br>
<br>
In any case you my initial assumption of 15% from uncontrolled tests was definitely off.  But I still think 21% is a bit too high.  Based on my test it could be as low as 18%. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A> at: 11/28/02 7:24:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2498<br> <font color=#333333>(11/28/02 7:23:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7965.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Is 200dps sustained Possible?</span><hr size=1> One other thing about that thread that doesn't help this discussion is that the underlying goal of it seemed to be figuring how much better SCM3 was than normal specialization.  People wanted to know whether or not it was a worthwhile ability.  By now we don't care about that, we know that it's a nice jump over normal specialization.  For the purposes of this discussion, all we want to know is the total mana savings we can expect.  How it is split between SCM0, SCM1, SCM2, and SCM3 isn't really relevant. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 674<br> <font color=#333333>(11/28/02 7:40:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?t